    <h1>Receiving goods and redistributing stock</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Not only can you receive goods and replenish stock in the plentymarkets back end, but you can also do so with the plentymarkets app.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This page of the manual guides you through the process step by step. It teaches you how to set up and use these functions.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="100">1. Receiving goods</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can book in stock using the plentymarkets app. Note that the user needs to have the right to book in stock. In addition, users can be granted the right to edit the purchase price when booking in items. Alternatively, either the <strong>Net purchase price</strong> saved in the <strong>Settings</strong> tab of the variation or the average net purchase price is inserted.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Hardware for the plentymarkets app</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Check the <a href="/en/welcome/quick-start/quick-start-system-requirements">system requirements</a> page of the manual to see current hardware recommendations for booking in items using the plentymarkets app.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="200">1.1. Assigning rights for incoming items</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Users with admin rights can book in items in the plentymarkets app by default. Users with <strong>Back end</strong> access must be assigned the necessary rights.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Assigning the right to book in items in the plentymarkets app:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Open the menu <strong>Setup » Settings » User</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the account.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Mobile</strong> tab.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> If this tab is not shown, the account has admin rights.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Visible functions</strong> area, activate the option <strong>Incoming items</strong>.<br>
→ The individual rights for booking in items are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional:</em></strong> Assign additional individual rights. Note <a href="#table-app-rights-for-incoming-items">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
